<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9793> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9793" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Additions and Corrections. The name of Ser. Sulpicius Galba appears alone in the date on a recently published inscription of the Campanian magistri (De Franciscis, Epigraphica 12 [1950] 126-130, pub. Dec. 1951), and probably gives an indication of the period after the condemnation of Hortensius and before the election of Aurelius Scaurus as Consul Suffectus." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8678> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8678" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 745, footnote 227" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7234> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7234" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 108. Sumner dates his praetorship and command in Hisp. Ult. from 111 into 109 (Orators 72), when he was succeeded by Q. Servilius Caepio. Cf. MRR 1.540, 544. Cos. 108. His name is used without that of his colleague in an inscription of the Campanian magistri (A. de Franciscis, Epigraphica 12, 1950, 126-130) to mark the date, which may therefore fall within the period between the condemnation of Hortensius and the election of M. Aurelius Scaurus (215) as Cos. suff. in 108. See MRR 1.548.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3477> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3477" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "CIL 1\n     .2.675, 676, cf. 694, 695; Fast. Ant., Degrassi 162f. ([S])er. Sulpici. Galba); Cic. Rab. Perd. 21; Obseq. 40 (Servio Galba); Chr. 354 (Calva); Fast. Hyd. (Sulpicio), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod. See Degrassi 54f., 127, 476f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3476> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3476" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 111, Praetors, and note 3, on Hortensius. On the filiation of Sulpicius, see RE nos. 57 and 58, and note SIG(3) 705, I, line 5, for a possible restoration." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3452> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3452" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "May have continued in command of Farther Spain (see 111, Praetors), if Caepio (Cos. 106, Pr. by 109) was his successor." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3435> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3435" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Successor of Piso (App. Ib. 99; see 112, Praetors and note 4)." .
